Bat Cave Mid Low Exterior Entrance

This mobile catapult design uses a bow to provide the stored tension needed for the firing mechanism. It is relatively easy to operate, and can deliver 15kg stone projectiles to a distance of about 250 meters with deadly precision. A crew of 3 is more than enough to provide a respectable firing rate of about 1 shot per  minute.
Two arrows pierce the dead man's back.

LORE SUCCESS!!! The great wooden palisade of Caer Corwell loom above you. The strongest outpost of the High Kings of the Moonshae Isles outside of Caer Callidyrr itself, the fort has never been taken by hostile forces, even during the Darkwalker Wars of 1345DR.

LORE SUCCESS!!! Within this grove and amongst the great standing stones, you see a crystal-clear pool of water which seems to emit a pure, bright light. It is a Moonwell. The Earthmother, beloved goddess of the Ffolk peoples, manifests her influence through these wells and through the druids who tend them in devotion to her and to the natural order that she represents.
